<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="827" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d827">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Files of the Division of Middle
                                Eastern Affairs: Lot 57–D178</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Telephone Conversation, by the
                                    Secretary of State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-30">December 30,
                                        1944</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Lord Halifax telephoned me this morning and during the course of our
                                conversation I mentioned to him the disappointment which we had felt
                                to learn that the British Minister to Saudi Arabia, Mr. <pb facs="0772" n="760" xml:id="pg_760"/> Jordan, had been returned
                                to his post.<note n="90" xml:id="d827fn90">Minister Jordan, who had
                                    been on leave, returned to Jidda about mid-November.</note> The
                                Ambassador seemed to understand and asked if I would leave it in his
                                hands.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>